 became project officer in developing the B-52 bomber and was one of the original team members on the Discoverer/Corona project &ndash; the nation&rsquo;s first spy satellite program &ndash; later inducted into the Air Force Space and Missile Pioneers Hall of Fame. He earned a master&rsquo;s degree from MIT and worked at Lockheed Corp., a leading defense contractor. Lieutenant Colonel Albert W. Johnson is the author of Rules of Chivalry for Nuclear War: How We Fight and Persuade Each Other. According to the book description, &ldquo;This book is meant to be a guide book for warriors of they are willing to think out of the box. It has some history, some fiction, some philosophy, some discussion of theology, some advice to young men about sex, and a little bit of physics. The center of the book is a proposal for "The Rules of Chivalry for Nuclear War" (The ROCNWAR). See Chapter 9 if you want to go directly to the proposal. The thrust of the book is that the characteristics of Chivalry are urgently needed when we engage in war."<BR/><BR/><a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/search/guide-book-for-warriors/'>guide book for warriors</a><a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/guide-book-for-warriors.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/rss_tiny.gif' border='0' /></a><a href='itpc://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/guide-book-for-warriors.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/itunes_trans.png' border='0' /></a> | <a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/search/how-we-fight/'>how we fight</a><a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/how-we-fight.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/rss_tiny.gif' border='0' /></a><a href='itpc://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/how-we-fight.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/itunes_trans.png' border='0' /></a> | <a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/search/air-force/'>air force</a><a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/air-force.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/rss_tiny.gif' 