<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Terrorism, safety and situational awareness</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">When the first aircraft struck the <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:PlaceName w:st="on">World</st1:PlaceName> <st1:PlaceName w:st="on">Trade</st1:PlaceName> <st1:PlaceType w:st="on">Center</st1:PlaceType></st1:place> what were your thoughts?&nbsp; Was terrorism your first thought?&nbsp; Or, was your first thought more like How could that happen?&nbsp; The first crash caught most people trying to figure out what human or mechanical error could have caused the crash.&nbsp; However, a little over 15 minutes later and the instant Flight 175 came into view we knew we were under attack.&nbsp; As the jet slammed into the <st1:PlaceName w:st="on">South</st1:PlaceName> <st1:PlaceType w:st="on">Tower</st1:PlaceType> of the <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:PlaceName w:st="on">World</st1:PlaceName> <st1:PlaceName w:st="on">Trade</st1:PlaceName> <st1:PlaceType w:st="on">Center</st1:PlaceType></st1:place> our view changed and the response of police and fire personnel to the WTC and the other incidents changed.</span></P>
