<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Civilian Law Enforcement Employees Tell Their Stories</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span style="COLOR: black"><font size=3><span  style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Hundreds of thousands of civilian personnel work in the criminal justice system, including state and local law enforcement. &nbsp;Generally speaking, civilian personnel are those who haven’t taken an oath of office and do not have a police officers power to arrest for probable cause. &nbsp;While most civilian police personnel are unarmed, some agencies employ civilian security personnel who are armed, but have only limited duties and powers of arrest.<o:p></o:p></span></font></span></P>
