<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Airman Missing In Action From WWII Identified </span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><font size=3><span  style="font-family: Times New Roman;">The Department of Defense POW/Missing Personnel Office (DPMO) announced today that the remains of a <?xml:namespace prefix = st1 ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags" /><st1:place w:st="on"><st1:country-region w:st="on">U.S.</st1:country-region></st1:place> serviceman, missing in action from World War II, have been identified and returned to his family for burial with full military honors.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span></span></font></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read On</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/airman-missing-in-action-from-wwii_17.html"><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/airman-missing-in-action-from-wwii_17.html</span></A></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Command Sergeant Major Wraps Up Tour </span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">The International Security Assistance Force's senior enlisted leader completed his 100th and final battlefield circulation Aug. 13. Since Aug. 4, 2009, Army Command Sgt. Maj. Michael T. Hall has traveled more than 265 days to various combat outposts, forward operating bases, camps and bases scattered throughout <st1:country-region w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Afghanistan</st1:place></st1:country-region>.</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read On </span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/command-sergeant-major-wraps-up-tour.html"><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/command-sergeant-major-wraps-up-tour.html</span></A></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">On chief petty officer leadership</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Yesterday, Coast Guard Commandant Adm. Bob Papp had the opportunity to address the Coast Guard Chief Petty Officers Association (CPOA). The CPOA gathers annually to discuss issues affecting the Service and to share leadership experiences. Adm. Papp took the opportunity to offer his thoughts on the role of a chief petty officer in today’s Coast Guard.</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read On</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://leadership-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/on-chief-petty-officer-leadership.html"><span color=#800080 size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://leadership-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/on-chief-petty-officer-leadership.html</span></A></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Medical crew takes flight, injured out of fight</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Five members of the 332nd Expeditionary Airlift Flight, with the help of other unit comrades, loaded a C-130 Hercules with medical supplies and equipment in preparation for picking up servicemembers at various locations throughout <st1:country-region w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Iraq</st1:place></st1:country-region>. </span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read On</span></P>
