<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P><BR/><BR><BR/><BR/>]]></content:encoded><comments>http://www.blogtalkradio.com/lawenforcement/blog/2010/08/18/american-heroes-press-top-stories-august-17-2010/#comments</comments><guid>http://www.blogtalkradio.com/lawenforcement/blog/2010/08/18/american-heroes-press-top-stories-august-17-2010</guid><pubDate>Wed, 18 Aug 2010 08:54:55 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>American Heroes Press Top Stories August 16, 2010 - Aug 17,2010</title><link>http://www.blogtalkradio.com/lawenforcement/blog/2010/08/17/american-heroes-press-top-stories-august-16-2010</link><description><![CDATA[<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Marine Casualty </span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span style="COLOR: black"><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read On</span></span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://terrorism-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/marine-casualty_16.html"><span color=#800080 size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://terrorism-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/marine-casualty_16.html</span></A></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Medical team trains for emergency response</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><font size=3><span  style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Air Force medical professionals participated in a massive joint forces field-training exercise recently simulating a terrorist attack in the <?xml:namespace prefix = st1 ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags" /><st1:country-region w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">U.S.</st1:place></st1:country-region></span></font></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span style="COLOR: black"><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read On</span></span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/medical-team-trains-for-emergency.html"><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/medical-team-trains-for-emergency.html</span></A></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Build the Mosque, it’s your Right</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><font size=3><span  style="font-family: Times New Roman;">The Muslim community has the absolute Constitutional Right to build a mosque near Ground Zero.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Moreover, by case law it is fairly clear that the “free exercise of religion” clause extends down from Congress to local governments.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>So, there is nothing legal that can or should restrict the building of a mosque. However, just as the mosque is legally indisputable, it is also an indisputable fact that 19 Muslims, in the name of fanatical Islam, murdered nearly 3000 American citizens at Ground Zero.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span></span></font></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span style="COLOR: black"><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read On</span></span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://terrorism-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/build-mosque-its-your-right.html"><span color=#800080 size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://terrorism-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/build-mosque-its-your-right.html</span></A></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Forensic Science and Crime Scenes</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span style="COLOR: black"><font size=3><span  style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Each week, millions of Americans tune in to watch CSI and CSI-Miami. Featuring the latest forensic fads and tools, these shows take a seemingly unsolvable mystery and unravel it in a primetime hour based on minute pieces of evidence to solve the crime. Just how do Forensic Teams and Labs accomplish these amazing feats?<o:p></o:p></span></font></span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span style="COLOR: black"><font size=3><span  style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read On<o:p></o:p></span></font></span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://www.police-writers.com/forensic_science_crime_scenes.html"><span color=#800080 size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://www.police-writers.com/forensic_science_crime_scenes.html</span></A></P><BR/><BR><BR/><BR/>]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Marine Casualty </span></P>
