<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">While many daughters may share similar interests with their fathers, one noncommissioned officer here relates the challenges of her job with an understanding dad. He's been there and done that. </span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read On</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/father-daughter-share-aircraft-heritage.html"><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/father-daughter-share-aircraft-heritage.html</span></A></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Anti-Leadership Lessons: Meg Whitman</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Imagine you are in an organization wherein one of your key leaders clearly does not share one of the primary organizational values.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Through their conduct, they have repeatedly, over the course of many years, demonstrated that they do not believe this key value is important.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Also imagine that the leader comes to you and now asks you to do, for them, this key organizational value.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>.</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><font size=3><span  style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read On<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span></span></font></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://leadership-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/anti-leadership-lessons-meg-whitman.html"><span color=#800080 size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://leadership-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/anti-leadership-lessons-meg-whitman.html</span></A></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><font size=3><span  style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Marking 20 Years Since <?xml:namespace prefix = st1 ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags" /><st1:place w:st="on"><st1:PlaceName w:st="on">Operation</st1:PlaceName> <st1:PlaceType w:st="on">Desert</st1:PlaceType></st1:place> Shield <o:p></o:p></span></font></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><font size=3><span  style="font-family: Times New Roman;">When Iraqi forces began pouring over the border into neighboring <st1:country-region w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Kuwait</st1:place></st1:country-region>, most Americans would have had a hard time finding the country on a map. <o:p></o:p></span></font></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Iraqi dictator Saddam Hussein ordered his troops to occupy <st1:country-region w:st="on">Kuwait</st1:country-region> on Aug. 2, 1990 – calling the oil-rich nation <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:country-region w:st="on">Iraq</st1:country-region></st1:place>'s "19th province." </span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read ON</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/marking-20-years-since-operation-desert.html"><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/marking-20-years-since-operation-desert.html</span></A></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Crime Analysis</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">These books on crime analysis or the use of crime analysis by police and law enforcement managers were written by police officers.</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read On</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://www.police-writers.com/crime_analysis.html"><span color=#800080 size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://www.police-writers.com/crime_analysis.html</span></A></P><BR/><BR><BR/><BR/>]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Father, Daughter Share Aircraft Heritage </span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">While many daughters may share similar interests with their fathers, one noncommissioned officer here relates the challenges of her job with an understanding dad. He's been there and done that. </span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read On</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/father-daughter-share-aircraft-heritage.html"><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/father-daughter-share-aircraft-heritage.html</span></A></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Anti-Leadership Lessons: Meg Whitman</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Imagine you are in an organization wherein one of your key leaders clearly does not share one of the primary organizational values.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Through their conduct, they have repeatedly, over the course of many years, demonstrated that they do not believe this key value is important.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Also imagine that the leader comes to you and now asks you to do, for them, this key organizational value.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>.</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><font size=3><span  style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read On<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span></span></font></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://leadership-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/anti-leadership-lessons-meg-whitman.html"><span color=#800080 size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://leadership-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/anti-leadership-lessons-meg-whitman.html</span></A></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><font size=3><span  style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Marking 20 Years Since <?xml:namespace prefix = st1 ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags" /><st1:place w:st="on"><st1:PlaceName w:st="on">Operation</st1:PlaceName> <st1:PlaceType w:st="on">Desert</st1:PlaceType></st1:place> Shield <o:p></o:p></span></font></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><font size=3><span  style="font-family: Times New Roman;">When Iraqi forces began pouring over the border into neighboring <st1:country-region w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Kuwait</st1:place></st1:country-region>, most Americans would have had a hard time finding the country on a map. <o:p></o:p></span></font></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Iraqi dictator Saddam Hussein ordered his troops to occupy <st1:country-region w:st="on">Kuwait</st1:country-region> on Aug. 2, 1990 – calling the oil-rich nation <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:country-region w:st="on">Iraq</st1:country-region></st1:place>'s "19th province." </span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Read ON</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/marking-20-years-since-operation-desert.html"><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/08/marking-20-years-since-operation-desert.html</span></A></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Crime Analysis</span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">These books on crime analysis or the use of crime analysis by police and law enforcement managers were written by police officers.</span></P>
