<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span style="mso-ansi-language: EN" lang=EN><font size=3><span  style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Man Admits Attempting to Use a Weapon of Mass Destruction to Bomb Skyscraper in Downtown Dallas<o:p></o:p></span></font></span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span style="mso-ansi-language: EN" lang=EN><font size=3><span  style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Hosam Maher Husein Smadi pleaded guilty today before U.S. District Judge Barbara M. G. Lynn to a felony offense related to his attempted bombing of a downtown Dallas skyscraper in September 2009, announced David Kris, Assistant Attorney General for National Security, U.S. Attorney James T. Jacks of the Northern District of Texas, and Robert E. Casey Jr., Special Agent in Charge of the FBI Dallas Field Division.<o:p></o:p></span></font></span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span style="mso-ansi-language: EN" lang=EN><A href="http://terrorism-online.blogspot.com/2010/05/man-admits-attempting-to-use-weapon-of.html"><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://terrorism-online.blogspot.com/2010/05/man-admits-attempting-to-use-weapon-of.html</span></A><o:p></o:p></span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span style="mso-ansi-language: EN" lang=EN><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Wisconsin Guard members join salute to Vietnam veterans </span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">More than 300 Wisconsin National Guard Soldiers and Airmen joined a statewide effort to honor the service and sacrifice of thousands of Vietnam veterans, thank them and welcome them home. </span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/05/wisconsin-guard-members-join-salute-to.html"><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://military-online.blogspot.com/2010/05/wisconsin-guard-members-join-salute-to.html</span></A></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><o:p><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</span></o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Soldier Relates to Iraqis' Hopes </span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">May 26, 2010 - The struggles of the Iraqi people to build a functioning democracy have been compared to the efforts of the American people during the Revolutionary War. This connection is especially strong for Army Spc. Scott D. Warren, a military police soldier serving here, who said he is a direct descendant of Army Maj. Gen. Joseph Warren, hero in America's war for independence. </span></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><A href="http://terrorism-online.blogspot.com/2010/05/soldier-relates-to-iraqis-hopes.html"><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">http://terrorism-online.blogspot.com/2010/05/soldier-relates-to-iraqis-hopes.html</span></A></P><BR/><BR><BR/><BR/>]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Army Casualty </span></P>
