<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><span size=3 style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Washington, D.C. Man Pleads Guilty to Attempting to Rob a Dunbar Armored Truck Carrying Over $2 Million in Cash Fired Three Rounds at the Truck; Entered a Home with Rifle in Effort to Obtain Getaway Car May 21, 2010 - GREENBELT, MD—Toumani Touray Thomas, age 33, of Washington, D.C. pleaded guilty today to attempting to rob a Dunbar armored truck containing over $2 million in cash and firing a rifle during the robbery attempt.</span></P>
