rch/civil-service/'>civil service</a><a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/civil-service.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/rss_tiny.gif' border='0' /></a><a href='itpc://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/civil-service.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/itunes_trans.png' border='0' /></a> | <a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/search/leaders/'>leaders</a><a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/leaders.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/rss_tiny.gif' border='0' /></a><a href='itpc://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/leaders.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/itunes_trans.png' border='0' /></a> | <a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/search/poker/'>poker</a><a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/poker.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/rss_tiny.gif' border='0' /></a><a href='itpc://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/poker.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/itunes_trans.png' border='0' /></a>  <BR/><BR/>]]></content:encoded><category domain="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/">leadership</category><category domain="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/">odd mind</category><category domain="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/">Raymond E Foster</category><category domain="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/">lapd</category><category domain="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/">magazine</category><category domain="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/">texas hold em</category><category domain="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/">lesa trapp</category><category domain="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/">los angeles police d</category><category domain="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/">criminal justice</category><category domain="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/">technology</category><category domain="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/">police technology</category><category domain="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/">civil service</category><category domain="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/">leaders</category><category domain="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/">poker</category><comments>http://www.blogtalkradio.com/lawenforcement/blog/2009/07/20/Leadership-and-the-Odd-Mind/#comments</comments><guid>http://www.blogtalkradio.com/lawenforcement/blog/2009/07/20/Leadership-and-the-Odd-Mind</guid><pubDate>Mon, 20 Jul 2009 23:09:24 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Sub Hunter - Jul 18,2009</title><link>http://www.blogtalkradio.com/lawenforcement/2009/07/18/sub-hunter</link><description><![CDATA[On July 17, 2009, Conversations with American Heroes at the Watering Hole will feature a discussion with Captain Edward M. Brittingham, USN (ret.).Captain Edward M. Brittingham, USN (ret.) “was in the Air Force ROTC in college, made pilot, but dropped out in his junior year. Drafted in 1962, he joined the Navy as a navigator (Naval Aviation Observer) and then reported to NAS Norfolk, Virginia for submarine training. He joined VP-10 and transitioned to the P-3A aircraft where antisubmarine warfare became the primary mission. He moved up the ranks ultimately to Commanding Officer of VP-11.” Edward M. Brittingham is the author of The Iranian Deception; Sub Chaser; and, Operation Poppy.<BR/><BR/><a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/search/american-heroes/'>american heroes</a><a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/american-heroes.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/rss_tiny.gif' border='0' /></a><a href='itpc://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/american-heroes.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/itunes_trans.png' border='0' /></a> | <a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/search/navy/'>navy</a><a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/navy.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/rss_tiny.gif' border='0' /></a><a href='itpc://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/navy.rss'><img src='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/img/itunes_trans.png' border='0' /></a> | <a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/search/naval-aviation-obser/'>naval aviation obser</a><a href='http://www.blogtalkradio.com/rss/tag/naval-aviation-obser.rss'>